                  <provenance>ʿAqbä Mikāʾel is mentioned in the
                     supplication formulas throughout the text; besides, in the conclusion of the
                     entries for the month Miyāzyā, on <locus target="#53rc">53rc</locus>, an
                     invocation mentions the scribe and "ʿAqbä Mikāʾel, the one who caused (the
                     book) be written".&#xD; In some passages, his name is replaced with the names
                     of Śǝʿǝlä Mikāʾel (esp. <locus target="#157rc">157rc</locus>, l.19) and Kǝnfa
                     Mikāʾel (esp. <locus target="#171ra">171ra</locus>, l.6).&#xD; Together with
                     ʿAqbä Mikāʾel, "his maid Walatta Māryām" is also mentioned (e.g., <locus target="#40ra">40ra</locus>, l.16, 40va, l.9, 88ra, <locus from="23" to="24">23-24</locus>).</provenance>
